        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 16 at 1:39PM EDT until July 16 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive
rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast Michigan, including the following
counties, Lapeer, Macomb, Oakland and St. Clair.

* WHEN...Until 445 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 137 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. This will cause urban and small stream
flooding. Up to 2 inches of rain have fallen. Rainfall rates
of greater than 1 inch per hour may continue for the next
several hours.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Pontiac, Imlay City, Romeo, Oxford, Almont, Capac, Rochester,
Clinton Township, Armada, Memphis, Dryden, Emmett, Macomb
Township, Lum, Rochester Hills, Auburn Hills, Attica, Lake
Orion, Brockway and Washington.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
